<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-305-908  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 305 908.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  April 2 1990 v12 n14 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Microsoft set on May 22 unveiling of Windows 3.0. (Microsoft Corpto introduce Windows 3.0 graphical user interface May 22 1990)(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Watt, Peggy.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Microsoft Corp will introduce Windows 3.0, the long-awaited updateof its DOS-based graphical user interface on May 22 1990.andP;  Newfeatures in Windows 3.0 include a 3D interface similar to that ofOS/2 Presentation Manager 1.2, a new icon-based Program Managerthat replaces the DOS Executive, and the ability to useprotected-mode memory.andP;  Several software vendors say they plan tounveil Windows 3.0 applications at Spring Comdex in Atlanta, GAand PC-Expo in New York CIty in Jun even if the interfaceintroduction suffers another delay.andP;  Users and vendors say theyare pleased with the improvements in Windows 3.0 but complain thatMicrosoft refused to use an industry-standard memory managementsystem, forcing many developers to rewrite their programs to runwith the new interface.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Product:   Microsoft Windows 3.0 (Graphical user interface) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Graphical User InterfaceMemory ManagementSoftware PackagesProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>